## Project Context

We are building and overhauling the **Spark Media Workstation** — a batch content production
command center at `app/static/pipeline_dashboard.html`.

The system serves a 12-channel YouTube content network (X71 Network). Its job is to:
1. Research business-relevant video topics with high monetisation potential
2. Generate a complete Pre-Production Asset Package (Phase 1) with full documented rationale
3. Present that package for human review with edit, amend, and export capabilities
4. On approval, dispatch assets to the GPU production pipeline (Phases B–H)

The Phase 1 output must be so thoroughly documented that an independent reader —
with no prior context — can understand every decision, assess the reasoning quality,
and re-perform the research from scratch if needed.

**Core principle:** The LLM is not a text generator. It is a senior YouTube strategist
that documents its thinking like a professional research analyst writing a brief
for a client who will scrutinise every line before signing off.

