## STEP 2: Amend / Edit Workflow

### 2.1 — Action Row Button Set

Place the following four buttons in the action row at the bottom of the Phase 1 review panel,
in this left-to-right order:

```
[ Reject & Cancel ]   [ Edit Assets ]   [ Export ]   [ Approve & Dispatch to GPUs → ]
```

- Reject: red border, red text
- Edit Assets: amber/yellow border and text
- Export: neutral grey border, grey text
- Approve & Dispatch: green background, white text, arrow icon

### 2.2 — Edit Mode Behaviour

When "Edit Assets" is clicked:

1. All static text display fields in the Phase 1 review panel transform into editable fields:
   - Single-line fields (titles, thumbnail overlay text): `<input type="text">`
   - Multi-line fields (narration blocks, rationale text, prompts): `<textarea>`
   - Use `contenteditable="true"` only as a fallback — prefer real form elements
2. The panel header gains an amber "EDIT MODE ACTIVE" badge
3. The "Edit Assets" button changes to "Cancel Edits" (reverts all changes on click)
4. The "Approve & Dispatch" button changes label to "Save Edits & Dispatch →"
5. All editable fields get a subtle amber left-border accent to make their editability
   visually obvious

### 2.3 — Per-Field Regeneration (Targeted Regen)

Add a small regenerate icon button `[↻]` next to the following fields:
- Each title variant
- Each thumbnail concept's ComfyUI prompt
- Each script section's narration
- Each script section's visual gen prompt
- Each script section's audio cue prompt

When clicked, a micro-prompt input appears inline below the field:
```
[ Instruction: e.g. "Make this hook punchier" ] [ Regenerate this field → ]
```

The agent sends only that field's current content + the instruction to the LLM
and replaces only that field with the result. All other fields remain unchanged.

### 2.4 — Save & Dispatch Payload

When "Save Edits & Dispatch" or "Approve & Dispatch" is clicked, the frontend
must collect ALL field values from the current DOM state — not from the original
LLM response object in memory. Build the dispatch payload by reading
`element.value` or `element.textContent` from each field at click time.

This ensures that manual edits and targeted regenerations are always captured
in the final dispatch payload.

